title: TAKE ALL Filter Test
story: dungeo
author: Sharpee Team
description: Test that TAKE ALL doesn't try to take items already carried

---

# Start at West of House
> look
[OK: contains "West of House"]

# Take the welcome mat first
> take mat
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# Open the mailbox so TAKE ALL has something left to take (the leaflet).
# NOTE: with nothing left to take, TAKE ALL currently produces blank output
# (platform: stdlib taking "all" emits no "nothing to take" message), and the
# transcript runner treats blank output as a failure — so we keep one takeable
# item in scope while asserting the already-carried mat is filtered out.
> open mailbox
[OK: contains "open"]

# Take all - should take the leaflet but not mention the carried mat
# (with a single candidate, TAKE ALL prints the bare "Taken." form)
> take all
[OK: contains "Taken"]
[OK: not contains "mat"]
[OK: not contains "already"]

# Verify we have both the mat and the leaflet
> i
[OK: contains "mat"]
[OK: contains "leaflet"]
